cs.CR, cs.OS, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper deals with the security of enclaves and the design of a filesystem interface for them. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the integration of the filesystem with the operating system and the support for real applications, which suggests that cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) are also relevant categories. The paper presents a formal proof of the safety properties of the filesystem, which indicates that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper discusses the design of the filesystem interface, which suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) may also be a relevant category.
